        <headline>Tornado Warning issued May 16 at 3:31PM CDT until May 16 at 4:00PM CDT by NWS St Louis MO</headline>
        <description>At 331 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm capable of producing a tornado
was located near Patoka, or 14 miles southeast of Greenville, moving
northeast at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Tornado and quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated rotation.

IMPACT...Flying debris will be dangerous to those caught without
shelter. Mobile homes will be damaged or destroyed.
Damage to roofs, windows and vehicles will occur. Tree
damage is likely.

Locations impacted include...
Kinmundy, Brownstown, Patoka, Shobonier, Pittsburg, St. Peter,
Vernon and St. Paul.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 70 in Illinois near exit 68.
Interstate 57 in Illinois near exit 127.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead
to flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
